17:45 - Metasploit VSFTPD backdoor → root shell
18:00 - hashdump, proof.txt extraction
18:15 - OpenVAS baseline (17 High vulns)
18:45 - Remediation + OpenVAS rescan (0 vulns)

Technical Findings

CVE-2011-2523: vsftpd 2.3.4 backdoor (:) → root shell

CVSS 10.0: Remote code exec, no auth required

Impact: Complete server control, data exfiltration

Remediation Plan

Immediate: Upgrade vsftpd ≥3.0.5, UFW deny tcp/21

Short-term: Patch management (unattended-upgrades), disable unused services

Long-term: Least privilege, network segmentation, vuln scanning (OpenVAS weekly)

Verification: OpenVAS rescans confirm zero critical/high risks
